t, Present and Uncertain Future -- t14 Casino Capitalism, Chinese Special Economic Zone and the Making of a Neoliberal Border in Northern Laos -- t15 ‘Old’ and ‘New’ Chinese Business in Cambodia’s Capital -- t16 Entrepreneurial Excursions: Short-Hop Chinese Migration at the Peripheries of Myanmar -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aNew Chinese migration is a recent development that has just entered an initial phase. An overarching theme and conclusion across the sixteen chapters in this volume is that China’s policy towards Chinese migrants has changed from period to period, and it is still too early for us to determine if Beijing will continue to pursue the policy of luoye guigen (return to original roots) or will revert to one of luodi shenggen (sink into local roots). The various chapters also show that the profile, motivations and outlooks of xin yimin (new Chinese migrants) have become more diverse, while local reactions to these new migrants have become less accommodating with increasing nationalism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2023) 0aChinesezSoutheast Asia. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Regional Studies.2bisacsh1 aAng-See, Teresita, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChang, Peter T.C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChiang, Bien, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChihyin Cheng, Jean, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChong, Terence, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHerlijanto, Johanes, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLaungaramsri, Pinkaew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLoh, Benjamin, econtribu